            "publication": {
                "license": "ORC",
                "remaster": true,
                "title": "Pathfinder Society Scenario #6-00: Salt of the Ocean"
            },
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p><span class=\"action-glyph\">2</span> The demon ark uses its actions on one of the following options (GM's choice). It loses one action from its routine if a PC succeeds at an attempt to Disable it or it reaches its Broken Threshold.</p><ul><li><strong>Broadside Blast</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">a</span> The demon ark makes a Chthonian cannon Strike.</li><li><strong>Demonic List</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">d</span> <strong>Effect</strong> The ship tosses and turns. Each creature in the hazard's area must make a @Check[reflex|dc:22] save. On a failure, it is knocked @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Prone]; on a critical failure it also takes @Damage[4d8[bludgeoning]] damage.</li><li><strong>Heads Will Roll</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">a</span> It makes a bowsprit Strike.</li><li><strong>Sea Chantey</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">a</span> (auditory) All fiends within 60 feet gain a +1 status bonus to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saves against fear effects; all non-fiends within 60 feet must succeed at a @Check[will|dc:20|traits:auditory] save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 1} (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 2} on a critical failure).</li></ul><hr><p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Sea Chantey]</p>"
